Winter meeting 2025

24w28

A new project is a new opportunity to reorganize my mess :D

2in/out <-> 4in/out

Here the idea is to somehow alternate between the two GS.

For reference, when the field is aligned with the axis, and keeping the OG parameters constants. I cannot really work with fields greater than 7mT before something explodes. We solved this before by artificially increasing the trap stiffness by a factor of 10.

Test 01 (The obvious)

Protocol Ilustration
1. Quench to 7mT in 60s.
2. Rotate in 60s towards the axis.
3. Rotate in 60s towards the axis.


Does not really work...

Test 02

This is again the same thing but... starting from an ordered 2in/2out state.

Protocol Illustration
1. From a 2in/2out GS, rotate to axis for 60s
2. Go back at the same rate

  • This case behaves a bit better, we can see a good increase in types I,VI vertices in contrast to test01
  • It is also really nice that we almost completely remove type IV vertices, so we end up with an almost fully charged state, with and some defects.
  • It also comes to my attention the plateau that forms when going back between 90-110 s which is the 45-75 degrees range.
  • It is noteworthy that the system fully goes back to the initial state, which is a good thing...

Some questions that might be important

Questions
  • The state on the axis is pretty stable. How different are they from each other? Is it always the same?
  • If the state is pretty much the same and controlled... can it still be used for the purpose that we wanted even if it is not the exact one that we wanted?

Test 03

Protocol Illustration
1. Rotate in 60s towards axis
2. Rotate in 60s towards axis
3. Rotate in 60s towards axis

Ok, so this is... not what i expect.

The first part is what I expected, and the second part for the most part as well.

  • When the field is on the axis, the forces go for the most part towards the center.
  • On the axis the same happens, but rotated.
  • On the rotation, the forces change a bit as the azimuthal angle changes, hence it makes sense for the hierarchy to change a bit.
  • Here we see that charges with are converted into . What feels strange is that it does not affect I and VI simultaneously as VI is basically constant.

Probar si z,y me lleva al estado complementario
Si hago el proceso al reves, me queda una carga positiva o negativa al centro?
Calcular el parametro de orden (de cargas) para el proceso forward e inverso y tratar de ver si se hacer una cosa chistosa de histeresis.
Como el tiempo inverso.

Probar ir de z a algun punto intermedio en el plano xy, perhaps al punto de conflicto

Probar subir un poquito mas el campo a ver hasta donde truene.
